\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 49. C. heterotrichum} Pancic,{\i  Elem. Fl. Bulg.} 42 (1883). Like {\b 48} but roots with fusiform tubers; leaves linear to narrowly oblong-lanceolate, dentate, sparsely to densely arachnoid-lanate beneath, with weak spinules c. 5 mm; capitula (1-)2-5, shortly pedunculate or crowded at apex, with 1-5 narrow subtending leaves shorter than capitulum; involucre 15-18 × 15-18 mm; bracts with weak spinule 1-2 mm, the vittae absent or indistinct.{\i  Damp mountain meadows. • C. part of Balkan peninsula.} Al Bu Ju ?Rm.
