\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 51. C. tymphaeum} Hausskn., {\i Mitt. Thür. Bot. Ver. } nov. ser., {\b 7}: 38 (1895). Like {\b 50} but leaves somewhat coriaceous, rigid, undulate, usually only shortly decurrent, lobed to pinnatifid, glabrous, usually sparsely arachnoid-hairy only on the veins; segments ovate-triangular, lobed or dentate, with strong spines (6-)8-16(-20) mm; capitula solitary or rarely in apical clusters of 2-3, shortly pedunculate; involucre (19-)22-25 × (21-)25-30 mm; corolla 23-24 mm; achenes c. 4 mm; pappus (15-)18-19 mm. {\i By springs and other damp places. • N. & C. Greece, S. Albania.} Al Gr.
